left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome

actor "Guest\n(unauthenticated)"            as Guest
actor "Candidate\n(system role USER)"       as Candidate
actor "Organization Member"                 as OrgMember
actor "OWNER"                               as Owner
actor "REPRESENTATIVE"                      as Rep
actor "HR"                                  as HR
actor "MEMBER"                              as Member
actor "Platform Administrator"              as PlatformAdmin
actor "SUPER_ADMIN"                         as SuperAdmin
actor "ADMIN"                               as Admin
actor "AI Service\n(CVerify.AI, HMAC client)" as AIService  <<system>>

note top of OrgMember
  GROUND-TRUTH §2: **"Recruiter" is NOT a role in this system.**
  Recruiting work is done by organization members holding
  OWNER / REPRESENTATIVE / HR. The four organization roles are a
  code-level vocabulary (`OrganizationRole` enum) — no entity
  property is typed as the enum; `OrganizationMembership.Role`,
  `OrganizationAuthority.Role` and `WorkspaceMember.Role` are
  plain `string` columns.
end note

note top of PlatformAdmin
  System roles are SUPER_ADMIN / ADMIN / USER.
  Only the Recovery controllers use `[Authorize(Roles=...)]`;
  Admin controllers use `[HasPermission("admin:*")]`, resolved
  through IAdminAuthorizationService (none of those permission
  strings are seeded by PermissionSeeder).
end note

Owner        --|> OrgMember
Rep          --|> OrgMember
HR           --|> OrgMember
Member       --|> OrgMember
OrgMember    --|> Candidate
SuperAdmin   --|> PlatformAdmin
Admin        --|> PlatformAdmin
Candidate    --|> Guest

