note as N_Unauth #ffdddd
  **GROUND-TRUTH §5.1 — verified unauthenticated but sensitive.**
  There is no global fallback authorization policy, so a missing
  attribute means genuinely anonymous:
  * `EmailTestController` — all 6 endpoints have **no auth attribute at all**
    (send-verification, generate-token, GET/DELETE `api/emailtest/logs`)
  * `SystemController` — all 6 endpoints, no auth attributes
  * `GET api/v1/ai-jobs/{jobId}/artifacts/{key}` — class-level `[AllowAnonymous]`
    ("allow internal microservice to call without bearer auth");
    any in-body guard is <<Not verified>>
  * `GET api/v1/candidate-assessments/dev-trigger` — `[AllowAnonymous]`,
    hardcodes user 019ecc1b-44e6-7600-803f-11249088ae92
  * `POST api/v1/admin/candidate-assessments/reprocess` (both routes) —
    `[AllowAnonymous]` on an admin route
  * `GET api/repositories/{repoId}/dev-reset-and-analyze` — `[AllowAnonymous]`
  * `POST api/auth/recovery/level2/vote` — `[AllowAnonymous]` on an admin
    quorum action; presumed token-gated in body, <<Not verified>>
  * `GET api/workspace/{slug}/members` is `[AllowAnonymous]` while the
    near-identical `api/organizations/{slug}/members` is not (§5.2)
end note

